         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">22/12/88 ¶  ¶ This morning, dear Mr. Wilson, I learn from Prof Allen, that already over 400 Doctors have inscribed their names for the Congress, ¶  so about 450 copies of the "select plants" ¶  will b...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">88.12.22a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Thomas Wilson</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">K88/12611, unit 394, VPRS 3992/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">The file includes a typed version of M's letter, made at the Chief Secretary's Office, headed 'Private'.</p>
               </note>22/12/88</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>This morning, dear Mr. Wilson, I learn from Prof Allen, that already over 400 Doctors have inscribed their names for the Congress,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Intercolonial Medical Congress of Australasia, Melbourne, January 1889.</p>
               </note> so about 450 copies of the "select plants"<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B88.12.01.</p>
               </note> will be required; but they cost (when merely stitched) only 2/ each to the Government.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>As it will take some time to write the dedication on <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">behalf of the Government into each copy,</hi>
               </seg> I hurry the official letter<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to A. Deakin, 22 December 1888.</p>
               </note> on at once, as you might wish to despatch it as early as possible. With best felicitation at this festive time to you and those dear to you.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
